  "body": "\r\n***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Autologin upon Status app launch happens despite the user tried to log in with the wrong password. This may lead to consequences of one (or more) accounts stuck in a deadlock with no ability to get to password input screen, thus making account unusable. Please see steps to reproduce below.\r\n**NOTE**: it's ok with Release 0.9.32 version. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNo autologin happens after an app starts for the account which tried to Sign In with 'Save password'=ON and invalid password\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAutologin happens after an app starts for the account which tried to Sign In with 'Save password'=ON and invalid password before\r\n<img width=\"256\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-12-26 at 19 27 54\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/50452741-aad4a700-0944-11e9-9ecf-bb60051af4f4.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1.  Install Status\r\n2. Create new account with password `123456` (UserA)\r\n3.  Create second account with password `123456` (UserB)\r\n4.  UserB logs out\r\n5.  UserB enables ’Save password until logout’ button and enters a different from valid password (e.g. `654321`). Tap ‘Sign in’\r\n\r\n**Actual result** = **Expected result**: ‘Wrong password’ tooltip appears above password field\r\n\r\n6.  Close Status app\r\n7.  Open Status app\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** ‘Wrong password’ tooltip appears. Means autologin attempt made with the wrong password used before for the account\r\n**Expected result:** No autologin happens\r\n\r\n8.  Tap `<` -> `Other accounts` to navigate back to accounts list screen\r\n9. Navigate to UserA account. Type wrong password and enable ‘Save password’ option. Tap ’Sign In’\r\n10.  Close app\r\n11.  Open app\r\n12.  Tap `<` -> `Other accounts` to navigate back to accounts list screen\r\n13.  Tap on UserA\r\n \r\n**Actual result:** Blank screen with infinite spinner. No way to return back for iOS. From this moment there is no way to log in to UserA account because all the time persisting autologin with wrong password happens which leads to blank screen with spinner. App restarts, further logins with valid password to UserB nothing helps, - there is no way to log in to UserA’s account now.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop (2018122603); node 0.17.10-beta\r\n* Operating System: iOS \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
